<font color="#FF0000">RESPONSE TO ART</font><br>
<tt>Mon Jul 21  6:17:26 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Art,<br><br>
I appreciate your message and could never regard it lightly. <br>
There have been references made on this site to GI's remaining silent ever since their return from Vietnam. It seems that their silence is still necessary when it comes to certain topics - even if they have been greatly affected by these things. This site concerns Vietnam. It is not about &quot;drive by shootings&quot;.<br><br>
I am very much aware of the fallout caused by the subject of civilian casualties. Get a few veterans together, however, and they will talk about them. I have been in those places where this has occurred.<br><br>
I am not about &quot;placing blame&quot;. Since my words have created this perception. I will take responsibility for them. They are mine, as indicated by my name and email address.<br><br>
Strangely, it is with a great sense of relief that I can go back to being silent.<br><br>
Peace,<br><br>
Tom<br><br>

